# Citation discipline

## Per-stream rules

- **arXiv**  — preferred channel is the arXiv MCP. Window: last **3 months**.
  Same work across versions (`v1` / `v2` / `v3`) collapses to **one** entry.
- **Top venues** (ACL, ICML, NeurIPS, EMNLP, KDD, ICSE, FSE, ESEC, TSE) —
  window: **1 year** since the conference date. Cite via
  Semantic Scholar / OpenAlex / venue-specific proceedings scrapers.
- **GitHub** — Copilot-hosted MCP. Sort primary stars, secondary release
  frequency. Items with no releases sort by stars only. Tie policy:
  `cutoff_include_all` (final list may exceed 3).
- **Industry** — Anthropic / OpenAI / DeepMind / ByteDance / Alibaba /
  Tencent / Meituan. Source types: official blog, product docs, technical
  reports. Multiple sources covering the same capability stay **separate**.
  All industry items must carry an `uncertainty` field in `extra` since
  there is no official API.

## Institution preference

Agent-judged "top-tier" preference is allowed. Record the rationale in the
research report (the synthesizer prompt does this for you).

## Missing citation behaviour

Items without URL or DOI are dropped by the citation_audit hook and a
`citation incomplete` info event is written to the audit log.
